casebody.data:
Saro A. DE FIORE v. UNITED STATES of America. No. 5085. United States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. Sept. 6, 1955. Fred T. Tanquary, Pueblo, Colo., for appellant. Donald E. Kelley, U. S. Atty., and Robert Swanson, Asst. U. S. Atty., Denver, Colo., for appellee.

Before PHILLIPS, Chief Judge, HUXMAN, Circuit Judge, and SAVAGE, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Dismissed on court’s motion, for failure of appellant diligently to prosecute.
